OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FUnion rejects offer to stop
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25FChristmas rail strikes     
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Talks aimed at averting train strikes  
OL,6, before Christmas are expected to       
OL,7, continue on Monday, after the RMT union
OL,8, rejected an initial offer by the group 
OL,9, representing train companies.          
OL,11,FThe latest round of strikes by union   
OL,12,Fmembers at 14 train firms and Network  
OL,13,FRail is due to begin in eight days.    
OL,15,FThe Rail Delivery Group (RDG) said its 
OL,16,Foffer would allow for a 4% pay rise    
OL,17,Fthis year and another 4% next year.    
OL,19,FBut the RMT said the offer did not meet
OL,20,Fits criteria for pay or conditions.    
